nsole.log() work in Node.js?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &#xA;   &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ishtms/learn-nodejs-hard-way/master/chapters/ch02-your-first-nodejs-server.md#the-process-object&#34;&gt;The process Object&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &#xA;   &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ishtms/learn-nodejs-hard-way/master/chapters/ch02-your-first-nodejs-server.md#the-stdout-property-of-the-process-object&#34;&gt;The stdout property of the process object&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &#xA;  &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &#xA; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ishtms/learn-nodejs-hard-way/master/chapters/ch03-working-with-files.md&#34;&gt;Working with files&lt;/a&gt; &#xA;  &lt;ul&gt; &#xA;   &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ishtms/learn-nodejs-hard-way/master/chapters/ch03-working-with-files.md#what-will-the-logging-library-do&#34;&gt;What will the logging library do&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &#xA;   &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ishtms/learn-nodejs-hard-way/master/chapters/ch03-working-with-files.md#how-do-you-work-with-files-anyway&#34;&gt;How do you work with files anyway?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &#xA;   &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ishtms/learn-nodejs-hard-way/master/chapters/ch03-working-with-files.md#lets-get-back-to-files&#34;&gt;Let&#39;s get back to files&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &#xA;   &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ishtms/learn-nodejs-hard-way/master/chapters/ch03-working-with-files.md#a-little-more-about-file-descriptors&#34;&gt;A little more about file descriptors&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &#xA;   &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ishtms/learn-nodejs-hard-way/master/chapters/ch03-working-with-files.md#creating-our-first-file&#34;&gt;Creating our first file&lt;/a&gt; &#xA;    &lt;ul&gt; &#xA;     &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ishtms/learn-nodejs-ha